$interpreted: Lio: Angel, catch this~
Lio: Fun, right?
Angelia: Yeah, not bad~
Lio: Alright, think fast!
Angelia: Hold on, I'm not ready!
Angelia: I-I'm so sorry...
Nigel: Having fun, huh?
Nigel: Comes to the Slums and offers no help at all, just hangs out and plays with kids. Isn't that kind of shameful?
Lio: Nigel, it's not her fault! I asked her to—
Nigel: Lio, go back to the Big House.
Lio: ...*sob*...
Angelia: It's okay. You can go.
Naya: What's your deal? If there's something you want from us, go ahead and say it.
Nigel: Alright, then. Then why don't you go squash some buzzwings for me, they've been a pain lately.
Naya: Piece of cake. Give us half a day!
Nigel: Fine, let's see what you can do. The timer starts... now.
Naya: Oh, come on! What are you, five!?
Naya: Angel, let's just go!
Naya: Damn that Nigel! We'll finish this so fast it'll make his head spin!
Naya: Too easy! Time to go back and rub it in his face!
Naya: Here are your dead bugs.
Nigel: Pretty fast, but don't think you're done yet.
Nigel: You got to take the silk from their abdomens yourself.
Nigel: The clothes we wear are all made from that silk. You pampered nobles had no idea, did you?
Naya: Would you stop being so petty?
Naya: Angel, leave this to me!
Nigel: Hey, I'm talking to her, not you!
Naya: You little...!
Angelia: Naya, it's fine. I'll do it.
Nigel: What's the matter m'lady? Too hard for you?
Angelia: N-No... I'll get to it now...
Hyacinthus: Nigel, stop.
Hyacinthus: Stop messing with them, will you?
Nigel: Party pooper... Whatever, let's go.
Naya: Holt on a second, were you just toying with us!?
Nigel: Shut it, Queen Kong. In the Slums, I make the rules.
